1
00:00:10,767 --> 00:00:13,733
<i>Why are you touching me?
Who are you? I don't know you.</i>

2
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:15,633
<i> Why are you giving this to me?</i>

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,033
<i> My child.</i>

4
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,033
<i>Don't ever meet up
with Danilo again.</i>

5
00:00:23,167 --> 00:00:24,867
<i>I will love you,
and I will never betray you.</i>

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:25,867
<i> Please be mine.</i>

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,633
<i> I need to talk to Danilo.</i>

8
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:29,500
<i> No one can reject me!</i>

9
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:30,867
<i> Damn it!</i>

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,533
<i> She's a good kid.</i>

11
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:33,967
<i> I hope to meet her one day.</i>

12
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:36,600
<i> Let's pray for it to happen.</i>

13
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:40,200
<i>Remember, don't ever give up,
no matter how hard it gets.</i>

14
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:42,400
<i> I will never give up, Ador.</i>

15
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:43,967
<i> Thank you.</i>

16
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,700
<i> Are Wiro and Kutsy here?</i>

17
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:47,867
<i> My grandchild.</i>

18
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,667
<i>Did you know that Jade tried
to make me insane?</i>

19
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>I didn't know that Jade tried
to do that to you.</i>

20
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,367
<i>But why did you say yes
to marrying her</i>

21
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,833
<i>when I've only been missing
for less than six months?</i>

22
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:40,333
Get out of the way!

23
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:43,500
You're walking in the middle
of the road.

24
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:47,033
Why did Danilo and Emma choose
to meet here?

25
00:02:02,367 --> 00:02:03,467
So annoying!

26
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:14,833
Hello?

27
00:02:14,967 --> 00:02:16,667
<i> Jade, what happened to you?</i>

28
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,767
<i> You look like a disaster!</i>

29
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:19,933
You're all sweaty.

30
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:22,767
Did you find Danilo?

31
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:23,767
No.

32
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,367
I lost him.

33
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,000
But I'm sure he's close by.

34
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:30,567
Wait!

35
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:36,700
Damn you!

36
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:39,433
This thing is useless!

37
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:42,567
Can't you ask anyone for help?

38
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:44,500
Okay, bye. I'll call you later.

39
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:51,633
Your car is here.

40
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:56,400
So that means you're somewhere
around here.

41
00:02:57,467 --> 00:02:59,567
I'm gonna find you, Danilo.

42
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:05,700
Emma,

43
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,667
I was trapped.

44
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:13,500
I didn't want Jade to look like
a fool in front of many people.

45
00:03:13,633 --> 00:03:15,000
Why didn't you cancel
the engagement?

46
00:03:15,133 --> 00:03:16,333
Why did you go ahead with it?

47
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:18,533
Because I thought you abandoned
us.

48
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:20,900
Emma,

49
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,300
I have been lonely
since you've been gone.

50
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:28,000
I was in a lot of pain.

51
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:30,067
I was lonely,

52
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,433
and when you were gone,

53
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,633
Jade was there for me.

54
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:37,267
She was with me the whole time.

55
00:03:38,467 --> 00:03:44,000
But it doesn't mean
that I love her.

56
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:48,300
I admit I tried to love her.

57
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:51,700
But I can't.

58
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,133
It's still you.

59
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:57,133
My heart still longs for you.

60
00:04:00,433 --> 00:04:05,700
That's why I almost died out of
anger when I saw you with Logan.

61
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,133
I was jealous.

62
00:04:07,267 --> 00:04:08,600
It was painful.

63
00:04:08,733 --> 00:04:11,200
It hurts to see you with him.

64
00:04:12,267 --> 00:04:15,100
You can get mad at me.
I will take that.

65
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:16,967
Because I made a big mistake.

66
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,533
But now that you're here...

67
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,533
I want to make everything right.

68
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:29,167
And I will ask you
for forgiveness every day.

69
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:31,133
I will never stop, Emma.

70
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:33,733
And Emma,

71
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,100
I can't let you go again.

72
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:41,767
Never again.

73
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,433
No!

74
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:12,067
No!

75
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:15,233
No!

76
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:20,600
Emma.

77
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:26,200
I've been blaming myself.

78
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:29,733
I didn't do anything
to find you.

79
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:35,367
I didn't even think that you
were having a hard time.

80
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:42,067
I didn't realize that you could
never abandon me and Mookie.

81
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:45,667
I'm such a fool, Emma.

82
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:53,767
But I will never conspire
with Jade to hurt you.

83
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:56,767
You have to believe me.
I can never do that.

84
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:02,267
Dan, I admit I was mad at you.

85
00:06:03,567 --> 00:06:06,000
Because I was manipulated
by Jade.

86
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,733
I believed her when she told me
you left me for her.

87
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:11,733
We were both wrong.

88
00:06:11,867 --> 00:06:13,967
I couldn't show myself to you
and Mookie

89
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,833
because I wasn't strong enough
to defend you.

90
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:18,233
Don't blame yourself.

91
00:06:18,367 --> 00:06:20,033
If I showed up right away,

92
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:22,000
we wouldn't be in this
situation.

93
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,267
Emma.

94
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:35,333
Emma, I will take all the blame.
You can hurt me if you want.

95
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,900
I missed you so much.

96
00:06:45,267 --> 00:06:47,100
I missed you so much, Emma.

97
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:54,033
I know what I've done
is unforgivable, Emma.

98
00:06:56,433 --> 00:07:01,533
But I will wait for the day
that you can forgive me, Emma.

99
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:05,100
Until you can trust me again.

100
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:06,767
I will earn it back.

101
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:09,133
I want our family back together.

102
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:18,467
You're a bastard, Danilo.

103
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:22,133
After leaving Emma for Jade.

104
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,800
You're trying to fool her again?

105
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:30,233
Emma...

106
00:07:32,467 --> 00:07:34,433
I thought you just wanted
to take Mookie back.

107
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:40,533
Why are you getting back with
that cheating bastard?

108
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:54,500
I'm not asking for too much.

109
00:07:57,267 --> 00:07:59,867
I just want a family of my own.

110
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,100
I just want to be with Danilo
and Mookie.

111
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,500
Is that too much to ask?

112
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,867
Why are you doing this to me?

113
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:15,933
Am I asking for too much?

114
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:17,867
Why can't you give me
what I want?

115
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:22,067
How come Emma gets everything?

116
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,500
You're just like Ligaya!

117
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:32,067
You're just like my adoptive
parents!

118
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:41,700
You didn't want me to be happy!

119
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:44,400
You all want me to be miserable!

120
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:54,033
<i>Looks like the fight is over.
Someone already won, Olive.</i>

121
00:08:55,533 --> 00:08:56,833
Shut up!

122
00:08:56,967 --> 00:08:58,200
- Shut up.
- News flash.

123
00:08:58,333 --> 00:09:08,300
<i>You lost the crown.
Emma is the winner...</i>

124
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:11,400
Emma...

125
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:25,433
Let me explain everything that
happened between me and Jade.

126
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:27,333
Not to protect myself...

127
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,333
- Dan.
- I want to tell you the truth.

128
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,967
Listen to me.

129
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:34,933
You need to know how Jade tried
to drive me insane.

130
00:09:40,667 --> 00:09:41,300
Dan...

131
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,367
Jade is here.

132
00:09:47,667 --> 00:09:48,067
Hide!

133
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:56,533
Let's eat while we wait
for Aunt Jade.

134
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:58,167
Thank you.

135
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:02,433
So that's what your mom told us.

136
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:05,933
She said she was driven
to go insane at Havenwood.

137
00:10:06,067 --> 00:10:08,233
That's why she didn't show
herself right away.

138
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:11,933
She was scared that you guys
wouldn't believe her.

139
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:14,833
But Emma did her best.

140
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:16,467
Dear,

141
00:10:17,667 --> 00:10:20,633
when she got her sanity back,
she came back for you.

142
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:22,700
But...

143
00:10:31,167 --> 00:10:32,267
Mom?

144
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:34,800
Mom?

145
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:37,333
So that means...

146
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:41,100
It was my mom I saw that night.

147
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:42,767
You remember that?

148
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:43,767
You're right, Mookie.

149
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:51,733
So, that means I got mad at her
without finding out

150
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:52,900
the whole truth.

151
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:57,500
She even tried
to explain herself,

152
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:59,367
but I didn't believe her.

153
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:07,300
<i> Mookie.</i>

154
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:08,767
<i> Can you please leave me alone?</i>

155
00:11:10,167 --> 00:11:11,900
<i> I don't want to talk to you.</i>

156
00:11:12,033 --> 00:11:13,033
<i> Mookie, dear.</i>

157
00:11:13,167 --> 00:11:14,267
<i> Mookie.</i>

158
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:18,033
<i>I'm not leaving until you talk
to me.</i>

159
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:19,967
<i> I have proof to show you</i>

160
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,133
<i>that someone drove me crazy
in Havenwood.</i>

161
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:23,933
<i> It's the doctor's findings.</i>

162
00:11:24,067 --> 00:11:26,233
<i>And I'm sure Jade has
something to do with it.</i>

163
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:29,433
<i> Guard, please help me.</i>

164
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:31,367
<i> This woman is harassing me.</i>

165
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:34,767
<i>And once I get my daughter back,
we can leave this place.</i>

166
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:37,900
<i>We can go somewhere far
from here.</i>

167
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:40,167
<i>I don't care what others think
about me.</i>

168
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,467
<i> What matters is...</i>

169
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:42,800
<i> What is?</i>

170
00:11:46,867 --> 00:11:47,933
<i> Mookie.</i>

171
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:51,033
<i>I don't care if you run away
with that man!</i>

172
00:11:51,167 --> 00:11:51,967
<i> Mookie!</i>

173
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:53,933
<i> Mookie, listen to me, please.</i>

174
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:55,400
<i> You're wrong.</i>

175
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:57,933
<i>Nothing's going on between me
and Logan.</i>

176
00:11:58,067 --> 00:12:00,667
<i>- Jade is lying!
- What about me?</i>

177
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,200
<i>What I want is for you to leave!</i>

178
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:06,367
<i>I don't want to see you ever
again!</i>

179
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,433
<i> That's what I want!</i>

180
00:12:07,567 --> 00:12:08,500
<i> Mookie!</i>

181
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:09,833
<i> Mookie, wait!</i>

182
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:12,900
Mookie, don't be sad.

183
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:15,667
You're going to see her anyway.

184
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,333
You can clear all your
misunderstandings.

185
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:20,000
That's right, Mookie.

186
00:12:20,133 --> 00:12:22,400
Your family will reunite soon.

187
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:24,933
I hope so.

188
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:30,567
And I hope we'll see my
grandmother, too,

189
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:33,333
so we'll be all together
as a family.

190
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:34,533
Oh my.

191
00:12:34,667 --> 00:12:36,133
It will be a happier reunion

192
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:38,033
if your grandmother will be
there, too.

193
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,100
Right?

194
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:42,467
I miss my grandmother so much.

195
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:49,267
She didn't like me
that much at first.

196
00:12:49,433 --> 00:12:51,967
But I get where she was coming
from.

197
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:56,333
She just didn't want
Mommy Olive to get mad.

198
00:12:56,467 --> 00:12:58,667
But even though she didn't know

199
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,333
that I was her granddaughter
before...

200
00:13:00,467 --> 00:13:03,733
She treated me as her own.

201
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,033
Grandma has a different way of
showing her love.

202
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,933
Where did they hide you, Ligaya?

203
00:13:33,267 --> 00:13:35,000
Should I go to my granddaughter?

204
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:42,833
Should we inform Mookie
about our gut feeling?

205
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:44,133
That Jade might know
where she is.

206
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:47,833
Let's not get her involved.

207
00:13:47,967 --> 00:13:48,867
Since we're here,
we should tell her.

208
00:13:49,167 --> 00:13:51,833
We're not sure about it yet.

209
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:53,133
You know what,

210
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:57,433
I really wish
my grandmother is back.

211
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,000
Who's there?

212
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,567
Who's out there?

213
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,700
Come sit here.

214
00:14:41,067 --> 00:14:44,933
Mookie, don't be sad, okay?

215
00:14:45,067 --> 00:14:49,200
I have a feeling your
grandmother will show up

216
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:54,267
when she hears about Danilo's
reunion with Emma.

217
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:56,967
- Hopefully.
- Hopefully.

218
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:02,900
She must be missing my mom.

219
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:08,200
I really hope for the day
that we'll all be together.

220
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:14,733
I hope that my grandmother
is safe wherever she is.

221
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:21,767
Hello? Bestie!
I have something to tell you!

222
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:38,433
Ligaya?

223
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:39,700
Ligaya, is that you?

224
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:42,533
<i> You're alive!</i>

225
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,100
<i> And you're here!</i>

226
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:47,567
Don't be sad, Mookie.

227
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:51,833
One of these days,
we'll hear from her.

228
00:16:51,967 --> 00:16:52,533
Yes.

229
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:58,500
Is that you, Ligaya?

230
00:16:58,633 --> 00:16:59,900
<i> I'm here, Ador.</i>

231
00:17:00,967 --> 00:17:02,500
<i> Ador, help me.</i>

232
00:17:02,633 --> 00:17:04,100
Wait! I'll get you out of there!

233
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:05,033
Wait!

234
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:13,733
What's that?

235
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,067
Ligaya!

236
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,700
<i> Hurry up, Ador!</i>

237
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:23,167
Hey!

238
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,333
Who are you?

239
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:25,633
What are you doing here?

240
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:28,033
<i>Caloy, don't you dare hurt him!</i>

241
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,200
Ligaya!

242
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,667
I think someone's screaming
outside.

243
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,000
Ligaya!

244
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:56,200
<i>God, please, don't let Caloy
hurt Ador.</i>

245
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:58,833
<i> He might kill my husband.</i>

246
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:00,333
<i> Ador.</i>

247
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:04,100
There's a commotion outside.

248
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:04,933
You're right.

249
00:18:05,767 --> 00:18:07,033
Let's check it out.

250
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:11,333
Yes, Ma'am? Where are you going?

251
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:14,600
We heard something out there.

252
00:18:14,733 --> 00:18:17,467
It must be our neighbor.
They're renovating their house.

253
00:18:19,667 --> 00:18:20,767
She said it's your neighbor.

254
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:24,133
Calm down, guys.

255
00:18:24,267 --> 00:18:25,767
It's just our neighbor.

256
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:27,533
- Okay.
- Okay.

257
00:18:27,667 --> 00:18:28,633
Where are you?

258
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:31,800
I know that you're here!
Come out!

259
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:33,700
Where are you?

260
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:36,267
Come out here!

261
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:36,933
Jade!

262
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:38,133
Jade, what are you doing?

263
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:41,033
Where's Emma?

264
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:43,100
Get her out. Where is she?

265
00:18:43,233 --> 00:18:46,267
I'm here alone. Emma's not here.
She's not with me.

266
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,467
What are you saying?

267
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:50,133
- And why are you so dirty?
- Stop lying!

268
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:51,267
I'm telling the truth.

269
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,033
I saw you with my own eyes!

270
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,600
You were kissing!
You were all over each other!

271
00:18:56,767 --> 00:18:58,467
I'm all alone.

272
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,433
Jade!

273
00:18:59,567 --> 00:19:00,333
What's this?

274
00:19:01,533 --> 00:19:03,033
Whose bag is this?

275
00:19:03,167 --> 00:19:04,567
Jade, what are you doing?

276
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:12,900
Jade, can you please stop?
Stop this!

277
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:15,300
I don't believe you!

278
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:17,133
I know that Emma's here!

279
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:21,367
If it's just you, what are you
doing here?

280
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:22,633
Why are you here?

281
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:24,633
Because I want to think.

282
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:26,433
And why did you follow me?

283
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:29,100
Can you leave me alone, Jade?

284
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:30,233
Come on.

285
00:19:30,367 --> 00:19:31,733
Let go of me!

286
00:19:31,867 --> 00:19:32,500
Let's go!

287
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:34,367
I can go home by myself.

288
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:48,567
It's your turn to make a fool
of yourself, Jade.

289
00:19:49,533 --> 00:19:52,633
You bastard,
are you following me?

290
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:54,533
What are you doing here?

291
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,767
You bastard!

292
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:19,433
You animal! Monster!

293
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:23,067
You don't deserve to live here!

294
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:28,300
You belong to the jungle!
Come here!

295
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:30,300
There's a fight.

296
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:32,533
- Look at Grandfather!
- Take a video!

297
00:20:32,667 --> 00:20:33,800
Grandfather is hardcore!

298
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:36,533
Look, he beat that guy up!

299
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:40,000
What a wuss!

300
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,433
Emma, Jade is gone.

301
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:02,000
She's gone.

302
00:21:03,767 --> 00:21:05,033
Did you follow Emma here?

303
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:09,133
Don't meddle in our business,
Logan.

304
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:14,767
After you betrayed her and left
her for her crazy sister,

305
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:17,633
you want to get back together
like nothing happened?

306
00:21:17,767 --> 00:21:18,500
The audacity!

307
00:21:18,633 --> 00:21:20,067
You don't know the whole story.

308
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:23,233
So don't get involved.

309
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:27,967
I thank you for helping Emma.

310
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:32,200
But can you please let us
solve our own issues?

311
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:35,067
Let Emma make her own decision.

312
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,200
No way.

313
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:42,200
I won't stop meddling until you
leave Emma alone.

314
00:21:44,033 --> 00:21:45,167
Is that what Emma wants?

315
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,400
Why don't you ask her
what she wants?

316
00:21:50,067 --> 00:21:51,733
Ask her who she loves.

317
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,500
Because I have a feeling

318
00:21:56,533 --> 00:21:58,667
that her heart still belongs
to me.

319
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:00,833
Not you.

320
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,567
Emma has a better life now.

321
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:11,400
But you're ruining it for her.

322
00:22:12,433 --> 00:22:14,400
You know how ruthless I am.

323
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:19,167
But I can be cruel if someone
tries to ruin her.

324
00:22:21,033 --> 00:22:22,467
So leave her alone!

325
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:28,567
I'm not afraid of you!

326
00:22:28,867 --> 00:22:30,967
I can be ruthless, too!

327
00:22:42,133 --> 00:22:42,900
What now?

328
00:22:44,133 --> 00:22:45,667
Can you fight without your gun?

329
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,533
You want to fight man-to-man?

330
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:07,900
- Sir, that's enough.
- Stop.

331
00:23:09,267 --> 00:23:10,933
You bastard!

332
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:13,300
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

333
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:15,767
She's only been gone
for a while,

334
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,400
and you moved on with someone
else!

335
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:19,200
Yes, I'm ashamed
of what I've done.

336
00:23:19,333 --> 00:23:21,300
I feel guilty for it.

337
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:23,800
And I regret what I've done,
Logan.

338
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:26,033
Because I made a big mistake.

339
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:29,467
I didn't try to find her.

340
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,933
I gave up.
I din't fight for her.

341
00:23:31,067 --> 00:23:36,333
Because I thought she was never
coming back.

342
00:23:36,467 --> 00:23:38,533
But that was in the past.

343
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:41,633
It's over and done.

344
00:23:41,767 --> 00:23:43,767
But I'm not gonna sit still

345
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,600
and do nothing to get her
forgiveness.

346
00:23:45,733 --> 00:23:47,267
To get her back.

347
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,100
And you!

348
00:23:50,033 --> 00:23:51,267
You have to stop, Logan.

349
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:55,400
No matter how much you try
to block me,

350
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:58,400
you can never stop me from
getting back with my wife.

351
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:02,167
Move!

352
00:24:18,667 --> 00:24:19,600
This is proof

353
00:24:19,733 --> 00:24:21,267
that Jade and Logan
are working together.

354
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,567
I will love you more than
he can!

355
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:24,900
You betrayed me!

356
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:26,167
The wedding will proceed
as planned.

357
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:29,333
She has many red flags.
he's almost like Mommy Olive.

358
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:31,767
You don't deserve
to be my daughter.

359
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:34,433
Or anyone's daughter!

360
00:24:34,567 --> 00:24:36,067
Grandmother!

361
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:37,267
Stop the wedding!

362
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,467
What are you doing here?
You're causing trouble again!

363
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:41,300
Stop this nonsense!

364
00:24:41,433 --> 00:24:43,400
There's not gonna be a wedding
today!
